WEBVTT

00:08.138 --> 00:10.445
- Previously
on "Dark Winds"...

00:10.575 --> 00:12.360
[loud explosion]

00:12.490 --> 00:13.883
- But that timer spring.

00:14.014 --> 00:15.319
That man was dying of cancer.

00:15.450 --> 00:17.365
Who'd want to blow him up?
- Who and why?

00:17.495 --> 00:18.627
How can I help you,
Mrs. Vines?

00:18.757 --> 00:20.933
- We had a burglary here,
someone who stole a box.

00:21.064 --> 00:22.196
I'll pay you to get it
and bring it back.

00:22.326 --> 00:23.632
[sheep bleats]

00:23.762 --> 00:25.808
You ever heard of
the People of Darkness?

00:25.938 --> 00:26.896
- A little out
of your jurisdiction,

00:27.027 --> 00:28.115
aren't you, Lieutenant?

00:28.245 --> 00:29.029
- You heard about
the truck bomb.

00:29.159 --> 00:30.030
The victim's Navajo.

00:30.160 --> 00:31.422
This belonged to my son.

00:31.553 --> 00:32.380
He wore it on the day he died.

00:32.509 --> 00:34.773
[gunshots]
- Ahh!

00:34.904 --> 00:35.731
- There's monsters everywhere.

00:35.861 --> 00:36.819
[gunshot]

00:38.734 --> 00:41.606
[ominous music]

00:41.737 --> 00:48.657
♪

00:56.143 --> 00:59.059
- [groaning]

01:17.120 --> 01:20.645
[groaning]

01:20.776 --> 01:23.344
[coughing]

01:23.474 --> 01:30.176
♪

01:44.582 --> 01:45.888
- Here.

01:46.018 --> 01:47.281
You're dehydrated.

02:07.997 --> 02:09.303
- [groans]

02:11.827 --> 02:14.917
- Just--just go get help.

02:15.047 --> 02:17.353
- You'll bleed out
before I get back.

02:17.485 --> 02:19.400
- That'll happen anyway.

02:19.530 --> 02:20.662
- Yeah.

02:20.792 --> 02:22.316
Maybe.

02:25.362 --> 02:26.494
Hey, stay with me.

02:26.624 --> 02:28.670
Come on. Stay with me.

02:28.800 --> 02:35.677
♪

02:41.161 --> 02:44.164
- Joe?

02:44.293 --> 02:45.948
[horn honking]

02:46.078 --> 02:47.428
Joe!

02:47.558 --> 02:50.779
[tires screeching]

03:10.494 --> 03:13.410
[moody guitar music]

03:13.541 --> 03:20.374
♪

04:01.719 --> 04:04.592
- [singing in Diné]

04:04.722 --> 04:11.599
♪

04:25.787 --> 04:28.616
[pensive guitar music]

04:28.746 --> 04:35.623
♪

04:36.363 --> 04:37.364
- Hey, Bern.

04:37.494 --> 04:38.756
- [speaking Diné]

04:38.887 --> 04:40.062
- I got your mail.

04:44.980 --> 04:46.286
Here you go.
- Thanks.

04:48.984 --> 04:50.028
- See you, Bern.
- Yeah.

04:50.159 --> 04:56.818
♪

05:01.997 --> 05:04.782
[giggling]
[thumping on roof]

05:07.176 --> 05:09.613
- Uh, what's Bigman doing
on the roof?

05:09.744 --> 05:12.442
- Trying to fix the TV antenna.
Moon landing's tomorrow.

05:12.573 --> 05:14.749
[speaking Diné], right?

05:14.879 --> 05:17.404
[sheep bleating]

05:19.623 --> 05:21.886
- Hey, did he
get it working yet?

05:22.017 --> 05:24.759
You know, my dad was
a lineman for NTOA,

05:24.889 --> 05:27.022
so I know about
that kind of stuff.

05:27.152 --> 05:28.676
- I think we're good.

05:28.806 --> 05:31.200
- Come on, man, I gotta
see the moon landing.

05:31.331 --> 05:32.810
It's important.

05:32.941 --> 05:34.464
They're gonna drive their
little space car around.

05:34.595 --> 05:37.075
- Bernie, Leaphorn for you.

05:37.206 --> 05:40.252
- It'll be there in three days.
You'll have plenty of time.

05:40.383 --> 05:42.385
Hi. Where are you?

05:42.516 --> 05:44.431
- Chee and I got into a mess.

05:44.561 --> 05:46.998
He's been shot.
We're at the hospital.

05:47.129 --> 05:48.652
[soft apprehensive music]

05:48.783 --> 05:50.175
- How bad?

05:50.306 --> 05:51.829
- Well, it went
through his shoulder.

05:51.960 --> 05:53.744
Doctors have him stabilized,
but he's gonna

05:53.875 --> 05:55.790
have to stay here a few days.

05:55.920 --> 05:57.879
I need you to come and take
a statement when he's up.

05:59.663 --> 06:01.186
- Well, aren't you there now?

06:01.317 --> 06:03.493
- Yeah, but, uh,
I have to run somethin' down.

06:03.624 --> 06:06.235
I'm pretty sure the man who
shot Chee was the same one

06:06.366 --> 06:08.890
who blew up
Emerson Charley's truck.

06:09.020 --> 06:11.153
Emerson's son Tomas
has something to do with it,

06:11.283 --> 06:12.633
and I need to find him.

06:12.763 --> 06:14.461
- Well, I'll check if
anyone's seen him around.

06:14.591 --> 06:16.071
- Chee got a good look
at the shooter.

06:16.201 --> 06:17.638
When he can think straight,

06:17.768 --> 06:19.466
I wanna know what else
he knows.

06:21.816 --> 06:22.947
- All right.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.645
I'll be there soon.
- All right.

06:24.775 --> 06:25.907
- Hey.

06:28.605 --> 06:29.911
I'm glad you're both okay.

06:30.041 --> 06:31.956
- Yeah.

06:32.087 --> 06:39.050
♪

07:06.034 --> 07:08.340
[ominous music]

07:08.471 --> 07:15.435
♪

07:38.414 --> 07:41.330
[baby crying]

07:54.125 --> 07:55.126
- Where were you?

07:55.257 --> 07:56.301
I was worried.

07:56.432 --> 07:58.390
- I'm okay.

07:58.521 --> 08:01.132
- Joe.
[sighs]

08:01.263 --> 08:02.917
Can you set the table?

08:09.140 --> 08:10.315
- Emma, I said I'm fine.

08:10.446 --> 08:12.274
- You don't look fine.

08:17.758 --> 08:19.847
The medicine man is coming
to the house today at 5:00.

08:19.977 --> 08:21.544
- I can't today.

08:21.675 --> 08:23.981
Just tell him
to come on Monday, okay?

08:45.742 --> 08:48.571
[somber music]

08:48.702 --> 08:55.535
♪

09:35.009 --> 09:37.011
- [speaking Diné] Bernie.
- [speaking Diné]

09:37.141 --> 09:38.186
- What you need?

09:38.316 --> 09:39.230
- Uh, just a pouch.

09:39.361 --> 09:42.538
- Okay, pouch. You got it.

09:42.669 --> 09:44.496
There you go.
No, no, no, no, here.

09:44.627 --> 09:46.673
Take that.

09:46.803 --> 09:48.065
- Is this all
for the moon landing?

09:48.196 --> 09:49.414
- Everyone's coming over.

09:49.545 --> 09:51.634
I'll save you a seat.

09:51.765 --> 09:54.245
You better take this too.

09:54.376 --> 09:55.246
There you go.

10:00.382 --> 10:01.426
Who's it for?

10:03.428 --> 10:04.995
- A friend's in the hospital.

10:05.126 --> 10:06.910
- Well, I hope your friend
feels better soon.

10:07.041 --> 10:08.390
- Have a good one.

10:13.090 --> 10:16.833
- Lieutenant Leaphorn,
it's good to see you again.

10:16.964 --> 10:19.009
I apologize for the
state of things here.

10:19.140 --> 10:22.491
I just got back in last night
and I'm trying to catch up.

10:24.885 --> 10:27.061
I'm sorry.
Please, what can I do for you?

10:33.589 --> 10:34.938
- This was in your lockbox.

10:36.766 --> 10:37.854
I'd like to know why.

10:37.985 --> 10:40.248
- No idea, I--
what is this?

10:40.378 --> 10:41.423
- This is my son's.

10:41.553 --> 10:42.816
He was wearing it
the day he died.

10:47.864 --> 10:50.214
- Yeah. Um.

10:50.345 --> 10:51.651
The Drumco explosion.

10:51.781 --> 10:54.131
I remember.

10:54.262 --> 10:57.961
I'm-I'm truly sorry
for your loss, Lieutenant.

11:00.355 --> 11:02.749
But there's-there's no reason
for me

11:02.879 --> 11:04.925
to have possession
of something like this.

11:05.055 --> 11:06.622
And there's certainly
no reason

11:06.753 --> 11:08.755
I would keep it
if I came across it.

11:08.885 --> 11:13.542
Y-you say you found it
in my lockbox?

11:13.673 --> 11:15.500
- We got a tip on the location.

11:15.631 --> 11:16.893
The buckle was nearby.

11:17.024 --> 11:18.808
- But not actually in the box?

11:20.984 --> 11:23.073
- We haven't
recovered the box yet.

11:23.204 --> 11:26.903
- So you assumed I'm capable
of something this ghoulish.

11:27.034 --> 11:29.079
- My son died
on what's now your property.

11:29.210 --> 11:32.343
- Three years before
I purchased the land.

11:32.474 --> 11:35.695
That's a lot of time for folks
to pick through the site.

11:35.825 --> 11:37.653
Explain something to me,
Lieutenant.

11:37.784 --> 11:41.526
The burglary we had here,
how is it your business?

11:41.657 --> 11:43.703
- Your wife hired
a private investigator.

11:43.833 --> 11:45.661
He came to me.

11:45.792 --> 11:48.055
- I wasn't even in town
when this break-in happened.

11:48.185 --> 11:49.970
Rosemary had to tell me.

11:50.100 --> 11:53.277
She has some conspiracy theory,
uh,

11:53.408 --> 11:57.107
about this crazy Indian church.

11:57.238 --> 12:00.415
I was a good friend of Dillon,
their chief.

12:00.545 --> 12:02.678
Even knew his family a bit.

12:02.809 --> 12:05.725
But, uh,
I-I can't imagine anything

12:05.855 --> 12:10.773
in my lockbox that would
mean a damn thing to them.

12:10.904 --> 12:12.644
- Did you hear what
happened to his brother?

12:12.775 --> 12:14.472
- Oh yeah, cancer.

12:14.603 --> 12:16.561
Horrible.
- No.

12:16.692 --> 12:19.434
He was murdered
day before yesterday.

12:19.564 --> 12:22.176
Somebody blew up his truck.

12:22.306 --> 12:24.091
[tense music]

12:24.221 --> 12:26.528
- Lieutenant, I-I am sorry
that you've been dragged

12:26.658 --> 12:29.531
into this mess,
and I'm even sorrier

12:29.661 --> 12:32.273
that it's brought up
painful memories.

12:32.403 --> 12:33.448
But...

12:35.450 --> 12:37.495
Wherever this came from,

12:37.626 --> 12:40.020
it's got nothing to do with me.

12:47.592 --> 12:49.812
- Thanks for your time.

12:49.943 --> 12:56.776
♪

13:11.965 --> 13:14.881
[cheery music]

13:15.011 --> 13:17.100
♪

13:17.231 --> 13:20.495
- Everything was in the box
according to Vines.

13:25.500 --> 13:28.111
What do you have to do
to get a Silver Star?

13:28.242 --> 13:31.027
- Way you talk sometimes,
I thought you had one.

13:31.158 --> 13:33.464
- Topped out at bronze.

13:33.595 --> 13:34.944
This the whole list?

13:35.075 --> 13:36.816
- Why? Is something missing?

13:50.090 --> 13:51.308
This your boy's?

13:53.397 --> 13:56.052
- Yeah. I found it up there.

13:56.183 --> 13:59.273
Chee got a tip that that's
where the box would be.

13:59.403 --> 14:01.753
There's a buncha
other stuff up there too.

14:01.884 --> 14:05.540
Guy who shot at us
was trying to burn it.

14:05.670 --> 14:07.368
- Mm.

14:08.891 --> 14:12.634
You got yourself involved in
some Navajo witchy witch here.

14:14.462 --> 14:18.205
There's a lotta talk about that
back when Drumco went up.

14:18.335 --> 14:19.989
- I remember.

14:20.120 --> 14:23.123
- This, uh,
People of Darkness business,

14:23.253 --> 14:26.169
you gotta keep that shit
on the rez, Lieutenant.

14:26.300 --> 14:27.910
Makes white folks uneasy.

14:28.041 --> 14:29.303
- What doesn't?

14:31.696 --> 14:34.221
- You know who
you should talk to?

14:34.351 --> 14:36.658
Your old man.

14:36.788 --> 14:40.401
Those peyote freaks used
to twist his panties, boy.

14:40.531 --> 14:43.230
Turned him cranky.

14:43.360 --> 14:44.535
Wasn't always cranky.

14:44.665 --> 14:46.798
- [scoffs] Hell he wasn't.

14:46.929 --> 14:52.065
The People of Darkness
doesn't explain the blond man.

14:52.195 --> 14:54.937
- Well, what does
the Charley kid say about it?

14:55.068 --> 14:56.156
- I don't know.

14:56.286 --> 14:58.201
He's in the wind.

14:58.332 --> 15:00.247
I got a feeling he's what
connects the dots

15:00.377 --> 15:02.205
between the truck,
the blond man,

15:02.336 --> 15:03.685
and the People of Darkness.

15:03.815 --> 15:06.079
- You got any leads?

15:06.209 --> 15:07.558
- No.

15:10.735 --> 15:12.346
Guess I gotta talk
to the old man.

15:12.476 --> 15:13.608
Can I keep this?

15:13.738 --> 15:15.958
- Sure.
- Thank you.

15:16.089 --> 15:17.655
- Tell Pops I said...
[speaking Diné].

15:17.786 --> 15:20.397
- [speaking Diné]
Okay.

15:23.052 --> 15:25.228
[knock at door]

15:25.359 --> 15:26.447
[door clicks open]

15:32.627 --> 15:34.324
- Leaphorn sent me
to take your statement.

15:34.455 --> 15:36.152
Said that you got
a look at the shooter,

15:36.283 --> 15:37.849
that you'd seen him earlier
at the rug market.

15:37.980 --> 15:39.199
- Yeah.

15:39.329 --> 15:41.375
Some white dude.

15:41.505 --> 15:43.943
Blond. Real blond.

15:44.073 --> 15:48.599
Pasty. Tall. Six-feet-plus.

15:48.730 --> 15:50.819
- So how'd he get away?

15:50.950 --> 15:52.212
- Truck.

15:52.342 --> 15:53.778
He had a pickup.

15:53.909 --> 15:55.606
- Make, model?

15:55.737 --> 15:59.393
- Ford, two-tone,
green and white, F-100.

15:59.523 --> 16:01.177
- Don't suppose
you got a plate?

16:01.308 --> 16:03.963
- Seriously?
This is what we're doing?

16:04.093 --> 16:06.966
No "how are you,
good to see you"?

16:09.011 --> 16:11.840
[coughing]

16:19.935 --> 16:23.852
Listen, I owe you an apology.

16:26.898 --> 16:28.683
- For what?

16:28.813 --> 16:31.599
- I put you in a bad spot
at the cave with Whitover.

16:31.729 --> 16:33.079
I...

16:34.950 --> 16:38.171
Under the circumstances,

16:38.301 --> 16:40.956
I don't know how we could
have played it any different.

16:43.959 --> 16:46.092
I'm sorry, Bernadette.

16:52.098 --> 16:54.883
- Did you have protection
with you?

16:55.014 --> 16:56.015
- No.

16:56.145 --> 16:58.756
I don't carry anymore.

16:58.887 --> 17:00.845
- I mean your...
[speaking Diné].

17:02.586 --> 17:04.588
That first day I told you.

17:04.719 --> 17:06.460
- I didn't, no.

17:06.589 --> 17:07.722
No.

17:15.208 --> 17:18.079
- Well...

17:18.211 --> 17:21.692
if you'd been carrying this,
you might not be here.

17:21.823 --> 17:24.130
- And if I wasn't here,
you wouldn't be.

17:39.797 --> 17:42.452
[soft apprehensive music]

17:42.583 --> 17:49.546
♪

18:04.866 --> 18:07.521
- [speaking Diné]

18:07.651 --> 18:10.263
[television playing
indistinctly]

18:23.014 --> 18:25.887
[both speaking Diné]

19:10.323 --> 19:12.151
- [speaking Diné]
I'm gonna give this to Dad.

19:26.339 --> 19:27.166
[speaking Diné]

19:33.259 --> 19:35.696
- You here for dinner?

19:35.826 --> 19:37.480
- [speaking Diné]

19:37.611 --> 19:39.656
I got a couple questions.

19:39.787 --> 19:42.093
Police business.

19:42.224 --> 19:45.880
- I still gotta solve
your cases for you, huh?

19:48.491 --> 19:50.624
- People of Darkness came up.

19:50.754 --> 19:53.279
Thought you might know
where I can find them.

19:53.409 --> 19:55.890
- Tribal Police
dropped the ball

19:56.020 --> 19:57.892
on those peyote freaks
when I left.

20:02.026 --> 20:05.639
They were called
[speaking Diné].

20:05.769 --> 20:10.339
They disobeyed the law,
held their meetings in secret,

20:10.470 --> 20:14.517
taking in [speaking Diné],
looking for a vision quest.

20:14.648 --> 20:17.433
That's not what
our people are about.

20:17.564 --> 20:21.089
They weren't like
the Native American church.

20:21.220 --> 20:23.222
They were real criminals.

20:23.352 --> 20:25.398
- You remember
who was involved?

20:25.528 --> 20:27.095
Anybody I could talk to?

20:29.053 --> 20:32.666
- I remember a lot of things.

20:32.796 --> 20:37.671
I remember dragging your hide
back to school too many times.

20:37.801 --> 20:41.892
I remember telling you,
"Make somethin' of yourself,"

20:42.023 --> 20:47.898
and here you are,
same place you were born.

20:48.029 --> 20:50.336
Worst decision you ever made

20:50.466 --> 20:53.991
was letting that woman
drag you back here.

20:54.122 --> 20:56.167
- She's my wife.

20:56.298 --> 20:59.170
Her name is Emma.

20:59.301 --> 21:01.782
And I'm doing
the same job you did, Pops.

21:01.912 --> 21:03.087
- Yeah?

21:03.218 --> 21:05.568
That's the problem.

21:17.493 --> 21:20.583
Go talk
to your friend's mother,

21:20.714 --> 21:23.369
Margaret what's-her-name.

21:23.499 --> 21:26.589
She knows all about
the People of Darkness.

21:36.730 --> 21:37.644
[door slams]

21:51.179 --> 21:54.095
- [speaking Diné]

21:59.927 --> 22:02.799
- [speaking Diné]

22:27.607 --> 22:30.392
[soft pensive music]

22:30.523 --> 22:37.356
♪

24:00.917 --> 24:07.794
♪

24:32.862 --> 24:34.951
Jesus, you look
like hell warmed over.

24:35.082 --> 24:37.432
- Mm, getting shot'll
do that to you.

24:37.563 --> 24:38.912
- Yeah.
Thought you might be hungry.

24:41.828 --> 24:42.829
- Thanks.

24:48.617 --> 24:49.923
What, no Jell-O?

24:55.450 --> 24:57.017
You find Tomas?

24:57.147 --> 24:58.758
- Nope.

24:58.888 --> 25:01.064
- Any leads on the blond guy?

25:01.195 --> 25:02.849
- Not yet.

25:04.241 --> 25:05.504
- You haven't gotten
any more talkative

25:05.634 --> 25:07.418
since I saw you last.

25:07.549 --> 25:10.900
- What exactly did Mrs. Vines
tell you about the burglary?

25:11.031 --> 25:13.903
- She said that Tomas Charley
took the box

25:14.034 --> 25:15.818
and they saw him do it.

25:18.342 --> 25:21.128
- Did she specifically
mention People of Darkness?

25:21.258 --> 25:23.522
- She believes
they're behind the whole thing.

25:26.786 --> 25:28.570
- Margaret Cigaret told me
that the People of Darkness

25:28.701 --> 25:31.225
might have reshaped themselves.

25:31.355 --> 25:33.706
Might still be in play.

25:33.836 --> 25:38.841
- Tomas Charley told me
BJ Vines is People of Darkness.

25:38.972 --> 25:42.062
Said that he's a witch
and that he witched his father.

25:42.192 --> 25:45.108
He blames him for the cancer.

25:45.239 --> 25:47.241
- Where'd he get that idea,
I wonder?

25:47.371 --> 25:50.070
- Rosemary Vines' theory
was that Dillon Charley

25:50.200 --> 25:51.419
gave her husband something.

25:51.550 --> 25:53.943
Emerson wanted it back.

25:54.074 --> 25:57.686
When Vines wouldn't give it
to him, they argued over it.

25:57.817 --> 25:59.906
- So Emerson
sent his son to get it.

26:01.647 --> 26:04.171
Question is,

26:04.301 --> 26:06.869
what does it have to do
with the People of Darkness?

26:11.874 --> 26:13.093
- Are you gonna finish those?

26:15.965 --> 26:17.314
- No, actually.

26:17.445 --> 26:19.229
You can have 'em.

26:23.669 --> 26:27.324
Bern and I are gonna go back up
to the malpais tomorrow.

26:27.455 --> 26:29.370
Maybe there's somethin'
up there we missed.

26:32.329 --> 26:33.853
I'll see you later.

26:33.983 --> 26:34.854
- See you.

26:42.905 --> 26:45.691
[baby crying]

26:47.606 --> 26:51.174
- I don't know what to do.
He's been crying all day.

26:51.305 --> 26:53.481
Please don't be mad.
Please don't kick us out.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.614
I just--
I don't know what to do.

26:55.744 --> 26:56.963
I'm not good at this.

26:57.093 --> 26:58.617
- Here. Let me see.

27:01.184 --> 27:02.359
Shh.

27:02.490 --> 27:05.449
Yeah. It's okay.

27:05.580 --> 27:07.887
Yeah. Yeah.

27:08.017 --> 27:10.411
Shh.

27:14.328 --> 27:16.635
[soft heartfelt music]

27:16.765 --> 27:19.550
He's just cuttin' his teeth.

27:19.681 --> 27:22.075
It hurts and he can't
make the pain go away.

27:25.992 --> 27:27.210
I'll make some [speaking Diné].

27:27.341 --> 27:34.304
♪

27:40.659 --> 27:43.487
[water running]

27:54.673 --> 27:58.241
When the [speaking Diné] cools,
just dip your finger in it

27:58.372 --> 28:00.113
and let him suck on it, okay?

28:16.738 --> 28:18.609
It's what Emma and I
used to do.

28:18.740 --> 28:25.007
♪

28:27.836 --> 28:30.665
- [speaking Diné]

28:40.327 --> 28:41.502
- [speaking Diné]

29:02.828 --> 29:04.090
- Emma Leaphorn?

29:07.180 --> 29:08.790
- Yes. How can I help you?

29:08.921 --> 29:11.880
- Mary Landon
with the "LA Times."

29:12.011 --> 29:14.317
I'm reporting on a story,
and a few women I've talked to

29:14.448 --> 29:15.405
said that
you might be able to help.

29:15.536 --> 29:16.755
- Help? How?

29:16.885 --> 29:18.495
- I'm writing about the effect

29:18.626 --> 29:21.237
of the Family Planning
Services Act on Indian women.

29:23.196 --> 29:24.719
I can protect your identity

29:24.850 --> 29:26.286
if that is what you are
concerned about.

29:28.505 --> 29:32.596
Can we schedule
another time to talk?

29:36.731 --> 29:38.341
- I don't think I can help you.

29:38.472 --> 29:40.126
I'm sorry.

29:40.256 --> 29:42.476
- Please.

29:42.606 --> 29:44.130
I know what you
are doing to help

29:44.260 --> 29:46.262
these young Navajo mothers.

29:46.393 --> 29:48.134
The world needs to know
what is going on here,

29:48.264 --> 29:49.483
what you are doing to help.

29:49.613 --> 29:51.137
I wanna help get the word out.

29:51.267 --> 29:52.747
- Get the word out?

29:52.878 --> 29:56.055
It's not about me or you.

29:56.185 --> 29:58.057
You wanna take
these women's stories?

29:58.187 --> 30:00.320
For what?

30:00.450 --> 30:02.409
So you could write something
about us poor Indians

30:02.539 --> 30:05.412
on the rez?

30:05.542 --> 30:09.372
These are our lives you are
playing with, our stories.

30:09.503 --> 30:11.505
You have no idea what it's like
to wake up every day

30:11.635 --> 30:13.028
knowing everything
you couldn't do,

30:13.159 --> 30:16.075
everyone you couldn't save,
not even your own--

30:16.205 --> 30:17.337
- What?

30:19.078 --> 30:20.688
What were you going to say?

30:22.037 --> 30:23.691
- Excuse me.

30:34.223 --> 30:35.877
- Hey.
- Hey.

30:36.008 --> 30:37.836
- [sighs]

30:37.966 --> 30:39.011
- Mm.

30:43.450 --> 30:46.105
- Carburetor?
- [groans]

30:46.235 --> 30:48.934
There's something wrong
with the throttle cable.

30:49.064 --> 30:50.761
- It's easier to check
if you take it out.

30:50.892 --> 30:53.547
- Yeah, I tried.
The screw is stripped.

31:18.354 --> 31:19.399
[sighs]

31:24.578 --> 31:25.840
Thank you.

31:28.625 --> 31:29.713
- [chuckles]

31:32.194 --> 31:35.154
- You're about eight hours
early for the malpais.

31:37.156 --> 31:38.984
- There's, uh, something
I wanna talk to you about.

31:39.114 --> 31:40.028
- Yeah?

31:45.860 --> 31:47.079
Border Patrol?

31:49.385 --> 31:50.952
- It's just an interview.

31:51.083 --> 31:54.564
- Why are you interviewing
for the Border Patrol?

31:54.695 --> 31:56.479
- Well, there's a law passing
through Congress,

31:56.610 --> 32:00.179
and next year, they have
to hire Native officers.

32:00.309 --> 32:02.094
- We have a border here,
Bernie.

32:04.966 --> 32:07.621
- Well, I passed
the lieutenant's exam.

32:07.751 --> 32:09.623
I'm ready to move up.

32:16.847 --> 32:18.632
There's nowhere to go.

32:18.762 --> 32:20.416
- Well, you'll get my post.

32:20.547 --> 32:23.550
All right?
Shit, I can't do this forever.

32:23.680 --> 32:26.118
- I appreciate everything
you've done for me, Joe.

32:26.248 --> 32:27.771
I do.

32:27.902 --> 32:29.425
And I'm gonna miss it here.

32:29.556 --> 32:31.558
But how many women
have made lieutenant?

32:31.688 --> 32:32.863
- Well, how many women
have they got

32:32.994 --> 32:34.561
down at the Border Patrol?

32:34.691 --> 32:35.823
You really think you're gonna
be better off down there?

32:35.954 --> 32:38.478
- I don't know,
but this isn't--

32:38.608 --> 32:39.479
- What?

32:43.396 --> 32:45.833
- I have to find my own way.

32:45.964 --> 32:47.661
- Why do you have to go down
there to find your own way?

32:47.791 --> 32:48.792
Why can't you
just find it here?

32:48.923 --> 32:50.185
- Man.

32:50.316 --> 32:51.839
- Ber--hey, Bern,
wait a second.

32:51.970 --> 32:52.971
Hang on.

32:53.101 --> 32:54.407
Bern, come on.

32:58.324 --> 32:59.325
[sighs]

32:59.455 --> 33:00.979
I'm sorry
if that came out wrong.

33:03.982 --> 33:05.200
Let me know
if you need a reference.

33:05.331 --> 33:07.420
I'll...

33:07.550 --> 33:09.639
see if I can find someone
to write one for you.

33:09.770 --> 33:11.163
[both laugh]

33:18.692 --> 33:20.520
- I'll be back in the morning.
- All right.

33:30.225 --> 33:33.054
[ominous music]

33:33.185 --> 33:40.018
♪

34:22.929 --> 34:25.846
- This look like
Navajo witchcraft to you?

34:25.976 --> 34:28.327
- It doesn't feel Navajo.

34:28.456 --> 34:30.503
Feels like someone
trying to be Navajo.

34:38.511 --> 34:39.641
Drumco.

34:39.773 --> 34:40.687
- Bag it.

34:49.739 --> 34:50.610
Bern.

35:17.941 --> 35:20.683
[ominous music]

35:20.814 --> 35:26.341
♪

35:26.472 --> 35:29.562
- Ugh. Is that Tomas?

35:29.692 --> 35:31.346
- That's my guess.

35:31.477 --> 35:34.349
[flies buzzing]

35:34.480 --> 35:41.313
♪

35:56.719 --> 35:58.852
Hey.

35:58.982 --> 36:00.767
We need to find his boy.

36:15.303 --> 36:16.957
[speaking Diné] Benny.

36:18.785 --> 36:20.700
- [speaking Diné]

36:23.659 --> 36:25.835
- Ooh.

36:25.966 --> 36:27.620
What do you got there?

36:27.750 --> 36:30.753
- I think my dad
left it for me.

36:30.884 --> 36:33.930
- Well, here,
let me help you with that.

36:34.061 --> 36:41.024
♪

36:51.470 --> 36:52.340
Ooh.

36:57.127 --> 36:59.042
Careful now. It's heavy.

36:59.173 --> 37:00.522
There you go.

37:06.876 --> 37:08.835
- Is it your birthday?

37:08.965 --> 37:10.967
- Sometimes he just
gets me things.

37:11.098 --> 37:14.014
Not usually girl toys, though.

37:17.322 --> 37:18.671
- Girl toys?

37:20.934 --> 37:24.590
- Uh, hey, Benny,
can I see it just for a sec?

37:24.720 --> 37:31.597
♪

37:38.560 --> 37:39.735
Bern.

37:44.784 --> 37:47.090
Get him in the car now.

37:48.657 --> 37:51.399
- Hey, Benny,
let's take a ride.

37:54.533 --> 37:57.797
- The lieutenant will
get it as soon as he can.

37:57.927 --> 37:59.886
- Bern.

38:00.016 --> 38:01.017
Get Henry.

38:01.148 --> 38:02.628
Send him here now.

38:02.758 --> 38:03.542
[engine turns over]

38:03.672 --> 38:07.981
♪

38:10.375 --> 38:11.593
- Sally.

38:11.724 --> 38:13.508
[baby cries]

38:13.639 --> 38:15.510
Do you know how
Father Sky and Mother Earth

38:15.641 --> 38:18.339
were brought together
with the lightning bolt?

38:18.470 --> 38:20.123
Sit.

38:20.254 --> 38:23.083
[baby fussing]

38:31.831 --> 38:34.312
The first [speaking Diné]

38:34.442 --> 38:38.490
was created
for [speaking Diné].

38:41.319 --> 38:43.886
She was crying,

38:44.017 --> 38:49.196
and [speaking Diné]
and [speaking Diné]

38:49.327 --> 38:52.591
wrapped her in clouds
and cliff rose bark.

38:52.721 --> 38:55.855
They put a rainbow high up
to protect her head

38:55.985 --> 38:59.902
and another rainbow below
for her tiny feet.

39:00.033 --> 39:03.428
Then they held her
between [speaking Diné]

39:03.558 --> 39:07.475
and [speaking Diné]
with a lightning bolt.

39:07.606 --> 39:10.086
- It's a nice story.

39:10.217 --> 39:14.569
- We have to make sure
our babies hear them

39:14.700 --> 39:16.223
so they don't forget.

39:20.009 --> 39:24.449
♪

39:24.579 --> 39:25.841
[line trills]

39:25.972 --> 39:27.365
- Scarborough
Community Hospital.

39:27.495 --> 39:29.149
How may I direct your call?

39:29.279 --> 39:30.977
- This is
Special Agent Ralston

39:31.107 --> 39:32.892
with the
Flagstaff Field Office.

39:33.022 --> 39:34.546
Uh, the FBI is investigating
the shootings

39:34.676 --> 39:35.938
out of the malpais yesterday.

39:36.069 --> 39:37.418
I was hoping
to interview the victim.

39:37.549 --> 39:39.202
- Oh, of course.

39:39.333 --> 39:40.726
Should I have someone
tell him when to expect you?

39:40.856 --> 39:43.468
- No, all I need
is his room number.

39:52.172 --> 39:53.826
[goat bleats]

40:03.836 --> 40:05.359
- You're just
gonna stand there?

40:14.194 --> 40:16.501
- Doll's loaded with Semtex.

40:16.631 --> 40:18.546
It's hooked to the pull string.

40:18.677 --> 40:21.244
- What kinda sick freak
would do somethin' like that?

40:21.375 --> 40:22.724
- Can you diffuse it?

40:31.820 --> 40:35.345
[ominous music]

40:35.476 --> 40:37.260
- Pliers.

40:37.391 --> 40:38.436
Needle nose, dum-dum.

40:38.566 --> 40:40.089
- You didn't say needle nose.

40:40.220 --> 40:42.135
- I'm saying it now.

40:47.445 --> 40:50.970
You need to pull
that metal bit out.

40:51.100 --> 40:52.319
- Why do I have to pull it?

40:52.450 --> 40:53.538
- My hands shake.

40:55.453 --> 40:59.108
You need to ground
yourself first.

40:59.239 --> 41:04.374
You spark that,
and we're both toast.

41:04.505 --> 41:11.120
♪

41:29.617 --> 41:31.706
Easy.

41:31.837 --> 41:33.491
Easy.

41:33.621 --> 41:34.404
Easy.

41:34.535 --> 41:36.972
- I'm being easy.

41:42.021 --> 41:43.413
- There.
- Jesus.

41:43.544 --> 41:45.285
- Safe.

41:48.593 --> 41:50.333
- What I do with it?

41:50.464 --> 41:54.207
- A good cop
would take it as evidence.

41:54.337 --> 41:57.210
You do what you want.

42:00.909 --> 42:01.823
Is that it?

42:03.303 --> 42:04.565
Come on.

42:04.696 --> 42:06.611
I'll give you a ride
to the station.

42:06.741 --> 42:09.222
Gotta get home in time
for the moon thing.

42:11.354 --> 42:14.096
[pensive guitar music]

42:14.227 --> 42:17.622
♪

42:17.752 --> 42:21.103
- [speaking Diné]

42:21.234 --> 42:23.062
- Cool your jets, man.

42:23.192 --> 42:25.804
- Astronauts Scott and Irwin
will take a drive on the moon.

42:25.934 --> 42:28.067
Can you make out what
we're seeing there, Wally?

42:28.197 --> 42:30.286
- That looks like
the ladder he'll come down.

42:30.417 --> 42:32.854
- I think we're seeing
the insulation,

42:32.985 --> 42:35.378
the orange insulation
and gold insulation

42:35.509 --> 42:36.989
across the equipment bay.

42:37.119 --> 42:39.078
I think we're
sitting here waiting

42:39.208 --> 42:41.341
for what Dave's immortal quote
is going to be.

42:41.471 --> 42:43.648
- Bet you it's gonna be
something about exploration.

42:43.778 --> 42:45.388
White guys love exploring.

42:45.519 --> 42:48.043
- What's the wager?

42:48.174 --> 42:49.915
- Two cups of Jell-O

42:50.045 --> 42:52.482
and a shot from that
tequila bottle in your desk.

42:52.613 --> 42:54.354
- You're bad.

42:54.484 --> 42:57.705
- And there he is.

42:57.836 --> 42:59.751
Hey, look at that.

42:59.881 --> 43:01.448
A perfect picture.

43:04.190 --> 43:05.713
- Okay, Houston.

43:05.844 --> 43:09.804
As I stand out here
in the wonders

43:09.935 --> 43:12.851
of the unknown at Hadley,
I sort of realize

43:12.981 --> 43:17.072
there's a fundamental truth
to our nature.

43:17.203 --> 43:19.118
Man must explore.

43:21.250 --> 43:22.295
- Hey.
- Hi.

43:25.690 --> 43:27.474
You take care of it?

43:27.605 --> 43:28.780
- Yeah.

43:34.176 --> 43:36.614
Hey, Benny.

43:36.744 --> 43:38.746
We're gonna keep your doll
for a little while.

43:38.877 --> 43:40.095
Is that all right?

43:43.838 --> 43:45.971
- What are we gonna do
with him?

43:46.101 --> 43:48.277
- I just made some calls.
Somebody will come pick him up.

43:51.193 --> 43:52.238
- I realized what this is.

43:52.368 --> 43:53.979
Arizona state seal.

43:54.109 --> 43:57.896
This is paperwork Drumco
had to file with the state.

43:58.026 --> 43:59.158
- Yeah, first thing tomorrow,
head over there

43:59.288 --> 44:01.029
and see what you
can make of it.

44:01.160 --> 44:08.080
♪

44:16.479 --> 44:20.832
You know the astronauts
used to train around here?

44:20.962 --> 44:24.792
A couple of years ago, an elder
found them out in the desert.

44:24.923 --> 44:27.969
They told him that
they were goin' to the moon.

44:28.100 --> 44:29.710
The elder asked them
if they could take

44:29.841 --> 44:31.930
a very important message

44:32.060 --> 44:34.149
from our people
to the moon spirits.

44:34.280 --> 44:37.892
The astronauts said okay.

44:38.023 --> 44:41.766
So the elder, he repeated
the message in Diné

44:41.896 --> 44:43.681
so they could say it perfectly.

44:44.856 --> 44:46.553
- What was the message?

44:48.076 --> 44:50.862
- [speaking Diné]

45:01.046 --> 45:03.570
- Why doesn't
she just call my dad?

45:07.617 --> 45:09.054
- She can't.

45:09.184 --> 45:16.061
♪

45:20.718 --> 45:22.589
- [speaking Diné]

45:35.341 --> 45:37.386
- And nice.

45:37.517 --> 45:39.867
Coming out very clean.

45:39.998 --> 45:41.564
- There's a car on the moon.

45:41.695 --> 45:44.916
[all cheering]

45:49.877 --> 45:52.750
[all groaning]

45:55.274 --> 45:57.929
- [speaking Diné]

46:07.634 --> 46:09.984
- For you to come back again
to the homes of men

46:10.115 --> 46:11.899
on the cool green hills
of Earth.

46:16.208 --> 46:17.600
- Thank you, Joe,
we're ready to...

46:17.731 --> 46:19.037
- Here you go, Benny.

46:22.518 --> 46:24.651
- Last week
I saw the astronaut.

46:24.782 --> 46:26.522
He was near our house.

46:26.653 --> 46:28.524
- Yeah?

46:28.655 --> 46:32.267
- He looked like that
but with lighter hair.

46:32.398 --> 46:34.792
I told my grandpa,

46:34.922 --> 46:37.272
and he said
to stay away from him,

46:37.403 --> 46:40.406
that he was bad.

46:40.536 --> 46:42.712
- Why'd your grandpa
say he was bad?

46:42.843 --> 46:46.934
- Because he blew up that well.

46:47.065 --> 46:49.328
- What well?

46:49.458 --> 46:51.547
- I don't know.

46:51.678 --> 46:54.550
[ominous music]

46:54.681 --> 46:58.467
♪

46:58.598 --> 47:01.470
[horn honking]

47:05.170 --> 47:06.388
- Yeah.

47:06.519 --> 47:09.348
[crowd chattering]

47:15.745 --> 47:18.183
Joe?

47:18.313 --> 47:19.445
What's wrong?

47:22.622 --> 47:25.320
It's okay. Just breathe.

47:25.451 --> 47:28.671
What the hell's going on?

47:28.802 --> 47:30.195
- It's the blond man.

47:30.325 --> 47:32.414
- What?

47:32.545 --> 47:35.853
- I think he murdered my son.

47:35.983 --> 47:38.116
[elevator bell dings]

47:38.246 --> 47:45.166
♪

48:05.970 --> 48:06.579
-Excuse me.
-Yes, may I help you?

48:06.709 --> 48:08.624
Have you seen an Indian?

48:08.755 --> 48:10.322
Jessica: Chee?

48:10.452 --> 48:11.584
He's here.

48:11.714 --> 48:13.368
♪

48:13.499 --> 48:14.674
Joe: He's at the hospital.[Alarm blares]

48:14.804 --> 48:17.111
He's coming for Chee.

48:17.242 --> 48:18.765
Let's bag
this son of a bitch!

48:18.896 --> 48:21.159
♪

48:21.289 --> 48:22.900
-[Screaming]
-There has been a spike

48:23.030 --> 48:25.772
in women being
involuntarily sterilized.

48:25.903 --> 48:28.209
Chee?
Chee, where are you?

48:28.340 --> 48:30.690
Thing about rabid animals,
they're unpredictable.

48:30.820 --> 48:31.778
[Grunting]

48:31.909 --> 48:32.822
♪
